,\nthe Jeans and Toomre stability criteria imply that the gas fraction must be\nlarge (> 2/3), consistent with the difference between our dynamical and stellar\nmass estimates. The implied gas depletion time scale (several hundred Myr) is\nsubstantially longer than the inferred mass-weighted ages (~50 Myr), which\nfurther supports the emerging picture that most stars in low-mass galaxies form\nin short, intense bursts of star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Jun 2014 20:00:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
